oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Three Enfield bullets in about .70 caliber and axe portions
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: These Enfield bullets are probably for the pre-war British musket and were imported and used by both sides early in the Civil War. These three were recovered in Ross Camp Ground near Mt. Carmel community of Hawkins County, Tennessee. Also portions of two axes were recovered from the site.
